{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase Statutory Sick Pay from \u00a396.35 to \u00a3233.10/week",
        "additional_details": "Statutory Sick Pay (SSP) is \u00a396.35/week. This means the average employee will earn just \u00a32.75/hr while off sick. \r\n\r\nThe average total pay, for employees in Great Britain was \u00a3518 per week in 2021. This means that while off sick, an employee is only entitled to just 18.6% of average weekly pay. (ons.gov.uk)\r\n\r\nPeople spend an average of 45% on rent per week. \u00a3233.10 is the minimum our government should pay, to ensure its citizens quality of life does not dramatically decrease while off sick.",
        "background": "Increase Statutory Sick Pay (SSP) from \u00a396.35/week to at least \u00a3233.10/week. On average, between 23-49% of an employees monthly salary goes towards rent alone, excl. every day essentials. Current SSP is just 18.6% of average monthly salary, an unrealistic number for anyone to live off of.",
